cyclone.name: ZETA
cyclone.current_location: about 450 miles south of the mouth of the Mississippi River
cyclone.trajectory: Turning north tonight, then accelerating north-northeast across the central Gulf toward the southeast Louisiana coast and the northern Gulf Coast
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: southeastern Louisiana near or just east of the mouth of the Mississippi River

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical Storm Watch west of Morgan City to Intracoastal City, LA
weather_observation.warning_coast: Hurricane Warning Morgan City, LA to the Mississippi/Alabama border, including Lake Pontchartrain, Lake Maurepas, and metropolitan New Orleans
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast from Port Fourchon, LA eastward to the Alabama–Florida border
weather_observation.wind: Damaging tropical-storm to hurricane-force winds likely late Wednesday afternoon through Wednesday night
weather_observation.storm_surge: 4–6 ft of inundation possible in and around Lake Borgne, Lake Pontchartrain, and the lower Mississippi River Delta including Plaquemines Parish
weather_observation.rainfall: 2–4 inches with isolated spots up to 6 inches, producing flash and urban flooding
weather_observation.other_hazards: A few tornadoes possible Wednesday and Wednesday night; very rough seas and dangerous waves will halt marine operations
